games.comment: Ryan Mathews was knocked out in the first half with a nasty-looking ankle injury. Mathews (5 carries, 26 rushing yards; 2 catches, 29 receiving yards) was carted off, but later returned to the sidelines and still had his pads on. According to reports, Mathews is fine.    Mathews' replacement,
Ryan Mathews (18-46) was the team's leading rusher.    Though Agholor dropped a pass that disrupted an early drive, he led the team in receiving (2-47) and also caught a touchdown.
